@@ -0,0 +1,88 @@
+# News reco reader (trade core)
+
+Purpose: mirror `trade:cache:news_reco_map` from Redis into an in-memory cache.
+
+Trade hot-path (gates/policies) MUST read only from memory.
+
+## How to integrate
+
+During trade process startup (when asyncio loop is running):
+
+```python
+from services.news_reco_reader import ensure_started
+
+async def main():
+    await ensure_started()
+    ... start your workers ...
+```
+
+Then inside gates:
+
+```python
+from services.news_reco_reader import get_reco
+
+snap = get_reco(symbol)
+if snap:
+    profile = snap.payload.get("suggest_profile")
+```
+
+## ENV
+
+* `TRADE_NEWS_RECO_READER_ENABLE=1`
+* `TRADE_NEWS_RECO_REDIS_URL` (fallback `REDIS_URL`)
+* `TRADE_NEWS_RECO_MAP_KEY=trade:cache:news_reco_map`
+* `TRADE_NEWS_RECO_POLL_MS=250`
+* `TRADE_NEWS_RECO_POLL_JITTER_MS=50`
+* `TRADE_NEWS_RECO_STALE_FAIL_OPEN_MS=5000`
+* `TRADE_NEWS_RECO_MAX_SYMBOLS=2000`
+
+## Fail-open behavior
+
+If Redis is down or JSON is invalid:
+- reader keeps last-good cache.
+If last-good is older than `STALE_FAIL_OPEN_MS`:
+- reader drops cache to empty (tighten signals disabled).
+
